{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":699,"text":"So if you've been following the news,"},{"time":2457,"text":"you've heard that there's a pack of giant asteroids"},{"time":4946,"text":"headed for the United States,"},{"time":6019,"text":"all scheduled to strike within the next 50 years."},{"time":9486,"text":"Now I don't mean actual asteroids made of rock and metal."},{"time":12539,"text":"That actually wouldn't be such a problem,"},{"time":14046,"text":"because if we were really all going to die,"},{"time":16150,"text":"we would put aside our differences, we'd spend whatever it took,"},{"time":19188,"text":"and we'd find a way to deflect them."},{"time":21318,"text":"I'm talking instead about threats that are headed our way,"},{"time":24020,"text":"but they're wrapped in a special energy field"},{"time":26156,"text":"that polarizes us, and therefore paralyzes us."}]},{"cues":[{"time":30506,"text":"Last March, I went to the TED conference,"},{"time":32410,"text":"and I saw Jim Hansen speak, the NASA scientist"},{"time":35246,"text":"who first raised the alarm about global warming in the 1980s,"},{"time":38156,"text":"and it seems that the predictions he made back then"},{"time":40621,"text":"are coming true."},{"time":42462,"text":"This is where we're headed in terms of global temperature rises,"},{"time":45949,"text":"and if we keep on going the way we're going,"},{"time":47558,"text":"we get a four- or five-degree-Centigrade temperature rise"},{"time":51026,"text":"by the end of this century."},{"time":52374,"text":"Hansen says we can expect about a five-meter rise in sea levels."},{"time":56162,"text":"This is what a five-meter rise in sea levels would look like."},{"time":59404,"text":"Low-lying cities all around the world will disappear"},{"time":62412,"text":"within the lifetime of children born today."},{"time":66210,"text":"Hansen closed his talk by saying,"},{"time":68506,"text":"\"Imagine a giant asteroid on a collision course with Earth."},{"time":72643,"text":"That is the equivalent of what we face now."},{"time":74996,"text":"Yet we dither, taking no action to deflect the asteroid,"},{"time":78770,"text":"even though the longer we wait,"},{"time":80479,"text":"the more difficult and expensive it becomes.\""},{"time":83556,"text":"Of course, the left wants to take action,"},{"time":85363,"text":"but the right denies that there's any problem."}]},{"cues":[{"time":88699,"text":"All right, so I go back from TED,"},{"time":90277,"text":"and then the following week, I'm invited to a dinner party"},{"time":93171,"text":"in Washington, D.C., where I know that I'll be meeting"},{"time":95636,"text":"a number of conservative intellectuals, including Yuval Levin,"},{"time":98378,"text":"and to prepare for the meeting, I read this article by Levin"},{"time":101974,"text":"in National Affairs called \"Beyond the Welfare State.\""},{"time":105340,"text":"Levin writes that all over the world,"},{"time":108539,"text":"nations are coming to terms with the fact"},{"time":110750,"text":"that the social democratic welfare state"},{"time":113051,"text":"is turning out to be untenable and unaffordable,"},{"time":116570,"text":"dependent upon dubious economics"},{"time":119134,"text":"and the demographic model of a bygone era."}]},{"cues":[{"time":122771,"text":"All right, now this might not sound as scary as an asteroid,"},{"time":125416,"text":"but look at these graphs that Levin showed."},{"time":128094,"text":"This graph shows the national debt"},{"time":130544,"text":"as a percentage of America's GDP, and as you see,"},{"time":133626,"text":"if you go all the way back to the founding,"},{"time":135707,"text":"we borrowed a lot of money to fight the Revolutionary War."},{"time":137823,"text":"Wars are expensive. But then we'd pay it off, pay it off, pay it off,"},{"time":141161,"text":"and then, oh, what's this? The Civil War. Even more expensive."},{"time":144213,"text":"Borrow a lot of money, pay it off, pay it off, pay it off,"},{"time":146946,"text":"get down to near zero, and bang! -- World War I."},{"time":149668,"text":"Once again, the same process repeats."},{"time":151370,"text":"Now then we get the Great Depression and World War II."},{"time":153278,"text":"We rise to an astronomical level, around 118 percent of GDP,"},{"time":157636,"text":"really unsustainable, really dangerous."},{"time":161316,"text":"But we pay it off, pay it off, pay it off, and then, what's this?"},{"time":165943,"text":"Why has it been rising since the '70s?"},{"time":168952,"text":"It's partly due to tax cuts that were unfunded,"},{"time":171745,"text":"but it's due primarily to the rise of entitlement spending,"},{"time":174439,"text":"especially Medicare."},{"time":176593,"text":"We're approaching the levels of indebtedness we had at World War II,"},{"time":179688,"text":"and the baby boomers haven't even retired yet,"},{"time":182679,"text":"and when they do, this is what will happen."},{"time":185949,"text":"This is data from the Congressional Budget Office"},{"time":187678,"text":"showing its most realistic forecast of what would happen"},{"time":190505,"text":"if current situations and expectations and trends are extended."}]},{"cues":[{"time":194620,"text":"All right, now what you might notice is that these two graphs"},{"time":197552,"text":"are actually identical, not in terms of the x- and y-axes,"},{"time":202183,"text":"or in terms of the data they present,"},{"time":203378,"text":"but in terms of their moral and political implications, they say the same thing."},{"time":207851,"text":"Let me translate for you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":209687,"text":"\"We are doomed unless we start acting now."},{"time":213354,"text":"What's wrong with you people on the other side in the other party?"},{"time":216334,"text":"Can't you see reality? If you won't help, then get the hell out of the way.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":220723,"text":"We can deflect both of these asteroids."},{"time":223004,"text":"These problems are both technically solvable."},{"time":226394,"text":"Our problem and our tragedy is that in these hyper-partisan times,"},{"time":229173,"text":"the mere fact that one side says, \"Look, there's an asteroid,\""},{"time":232165,"text":"means that the other side's going to say, \"Huh? What?"},{"time":234406,"text":"No, I'm not even going to look up. No.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":236984,"text":"To understand why this is happening to us,"},{"time":240088,"text":"and what we can do about it, we need to learn more about moral psychology."},{"time":244134,"text":"So I'm a social psychologist, and I study morality,"},{"time":246792,"text":"and one of the most important principles of morality"},{"time":249179,"text":"is that morality binds and blinds."},{"time":252429,"text":"It binds us into teams that circle around sacred values"},{"time":254863,"text":"but thereby makes us go blind to objective reality."}]},{"cues":[{"time":258776,"text":"Think of it like this."},{"time":259882,"text":"Large-scale cooperation is extremely rare on this planet."},{"time":263945,"text":"There are only a few species that can do it."},{"time":266104,"text":"That's a beehive. That's a termite mound, a giant termite mound."},{"time":269104,"text":"And when you find this in other animals, it's always the same story."},{"time":272204,"text":"They're always all siblings who are children of a single queen,"},{"time":277101,"text":"so they're all in the same boat."},{"time":278960,"text":"They rise or fall, they live or die, as one."},{"time":282281,"text":"There's only one species on the planet that can do this"},{"time":284572,"text":"without kinship, and that, of course, is us."},{"time":287147,"text":"This is a reconstruction of ancient Babylon,"},{"time":289418,"text":"and this is Tenochtitlan."}]},{"cues":[{"time":291741,"text":"Now how did we do this? How did we go"},{"time":293833,"text":"from being hunter-gatherers 10,000 years ago"},{"time":296827,"text":"to building these gigantic cities in just a few thousand years?"},{"time":300845,"text":"It's miraculous, and part of the explanation"},{"time":303888,"text":"is this ability to circle around sacred values."},{"time":308112,"text":"As you see, temples and gods play a big role in all ancient civilizations."},{"time":312036,"text":"This is an image of Muslims circling the Kaaba in Mecca."},{"time":315888,"text":"It's a sacred rock, and when people circle something together,"},{"time":319033,"text":"they unite, they can trust each other, they become one."},{"time":323404,"text":"It's as though you're moving an electrical wire"},{"time":325585,"text":"through a magnetic field that generates current."},{"time":327722,"text":"When people circle together, they generate a current."},{"time":330645,"text":"We love to circle around things."},{"time":332178,"text":"We circle around flags, and then we can trust each other."},{"time":335876,"text":"We can fight as a team, as a unit."},{"time":338717,"text":"But even as morality binds people together into a unit,"},{"time":341876,"text":"into a team, the circling blinds them."},{"time":345848,"text":"It causes them to distort reality."},{"time":347656,"text":"We begin separating everything into good versus evil."},{"time":351693,"text":"Now that process feels great. It feels really satisfying."},{"time":355591,"text":"But it is a gross distortion of reality."}]},{"cues":[{"time":359810,"text":"You can see the moral electromagnet operating in the U.S. Congress."},{"time":363218,"text":"This is a graph that shows the degree to which voting"},{"time":365450,"text":"in Congress falls strictly along the left-right axis,"},{"time":368281,"text":"so that if you know how liberal or conservative someone is,"},{"time":370957,"text":"you know exactly how they voted on all the major issues."},{"time":374183,"text":"And what you can see is that,"},{"time":376237,"text":"in the decades after the Civil War,"},{"time":378622,"text":"Congress was extraordinarily polarized,"},{"time":381111,"text":"as you would expect, about as high as can be."},{"time":383654,"text":"But then, after World War I, things dropped,"},{"time":386630,"text":"and we get this historically low level of polarization."},{"time":389535,"text":"This was a golden age of bipartisanship,"},{"time":391227,"text":"at least in terms of the parties' ability to work together"},{"time":394502,"text":"and solve grand national problems."},{"time":397510,"text":"But in the 1980s and '90s, the electromagnet turns back on."},{"time":401959,"text":"Polarization rises."},{"time":404800,"text":"It used to be that conservatives and moderates and liberals"},{"time":407766,"text":"could all work together in Congress."},{"time":409598,"text":"They could rearrange themselves, form bipartisan committees,"},{"time":412439,"text":"but as the moral electromagnet got cranked up,"},{"time":415712,"text":"the force field increased,"},{"time":417982,"text":"Democrats and Republicans were pulled apart."},{"time":420746,"text":"It became much harder for them to socialize,"},{"time":422733,"text":"much harder for them to cooperate."},{"time":424211,"text":"Retiring members nowadays say that it's become like gang warfare."},{"time":429052,"text":"Did anybody notice that in two of the three debates,"},{"time":432564,"text":"Obama wore a blue tie and Romney wore a red tie?"},{"time":436080,"text":"Do you know why they do this?"},{"time":438066,"text":"It's so that the Bloods and the Crips will know which side to vote for. (Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":442208,"text":"The polarization is strongest among our political elites."},{"time":444974,"text":"Nobody doubts that this is happening in Washington."},{"time":447152,"text":"But for a while, there was some doubt as to whether it was happening among the people."},{"time":450588,"text":"Well, in the last 12 years it's become"},{"time":451896,"text":"much more apparent that it is."},{"time":453983,"text":"So look at this data. This is from the American National Elections Survey."},{"time":457205,"text":"And what they do on that survey is they ask"},{"time":459845,"text":"what's called a feeling thermometer rating."},{"time":461857,"text":"So, how warm or cold do you feel about, you know,"},{"time":466094,"text":"Native Americans, or the military, the Republican Party,"},{"time":468869,"text":"the Democratic Party, all sorts of groups in American life."},{"time":471795,"text":"The blue line shows how warmly Democrats feel"},{"time":474477,"text":"about Democrats, and they like them."},{"time":476940,"text":"You know, ratings in the 70s on a 100-point scale."},{"time":479645,"text":"Republicans like Republicans. That's not a surprise."},{"time":482660,"text":"But when you look at cross-party ratings,"},{"time":484734,"text":"you find, well, that it's lower, but actually,"},{"time":487269,"text":"when I first saw this data, I was surprised."},{"time":489253,"text":"That's actually not so bad. If you go back to the Carter and even Reagan administrations,"},{"time":492548,"text":"they were rating the other party 43, 45. It's not terrible."},{"time":497125,"text":"It drifts downwards very slightly,"},{"time":499440,"text":"but now look what happens under George W. Bush and Obama."},{"time":503301,"text":"It plummets. Something is going on here."},{"time":506053,"text":"The moral electromagnet is turning back on,"},{"time":508454,"text":"and nowadays, just very recently,"},{"time":510614,"text":"Democrats really dislike Republicans."},{"time":512854,"text":"Republicans really dislike the Democrats. We're changing."},{"time":516370,"text":"It's as though the moral electromagnet is affecting us too."},{"time":519220,"text":"It's like put out in the two oceans and it's pulling the whole country apart,"},{"time":522945,"text":"pulling left and right into their own territories"},{"time":526901,"text":"like the Bloods and the Crips."}]},{"cues":[{"time":529710,"text":"Now, there are many reasons why this is happening to us,"},{"time":532724,"text":"and many of them we cannot reverse."},{"time":535644,"text":"We will never again have a political class"},{"time":538141,"text":"that was forged by the experience of fighting together"},{"time":541700,"text":"in World War II against a common enemy."},{"time":544444,"text":"We will never again have just three television networks,"},{"time":547978,"text":"all of which are relatively centrist."},{"time":551151,"text":"And we will never again have a large group of conservative southern Democrats"},{"time":555991,"text":"and liberal northern Republicans making it easy,"},{"time":559782,"text":"making there be a lot of overlap for bipartisan cooperation."},{"time":564100,"text":"So for a lot of reasons, those decades after the Second World War"},{"time":566748,"text":"were an historically anomalous time."},{"time":568551,"text":"We will never get back to those low levels of polarization, I believe."}]},{"cues":[{"time":572268,"text":"But there's a lot that we can do. There are dozens"},{"time":574866,"text":"and dozens of reforms we can do that will make things better,"},{"time":578012,"text":"because a lot of our dysfunction can be traced directly"},{"time":580436,"text":"to things that Congress did to itself in the 1990s"},{"time":584059,"text":"that created a much more polarized and dysfunctional institution."},{"time":589154,"text":"These changes are detailed in many books."},{"time":591346,"text":"These are two that I strongly recommend,"},{"time":593586,"text":"and they list a whole bunch of reforms."},{"time":595737,"text":"I'm just going to group them into three broad classes here."}]},{"cues":[{"time":598507,"text":"So if you think about this as the problem of a dysfunctional,"},{"time":601545,"text":"hyper-polarized institution, well, the first step is,"},{"time":604889,"text":"do what you can so that fewer hyper-partisans get elected in the first place,"},{"time":610163,"text":"and when you have closed party primaries,"},{"time":611557,"text":"and only the most committed Republicans and Democrats are voting,"},{"time":614621,"text":"you're nominating and selecting the most extreme hyper-partisans."},{"time":618617,"text":"So open primaries would make that problem much, much less severe."}]},{"cues":[{"time":622204,"text":"But the problem isn't primarily that we're electing bad people to Congress."},{"time":626955,"text":"From my experience, and from what I've heard from Congressional insiders,"},{"time":630355,"text":"most of the people going to Congress are good, hard-working,"},{"time":633335,"text":"intelligent people who really want to solve problems,"},{"time":635996,"text":"but once they get there, they find that they are forced"},{"time":638621,"text":"to play a game that rewards hyper-partisanship"},{"time":641552,"text":"and that punishes independent thinking."},{"time":643201,"text":"You step out of line, you get punished."},{"time":645779,"text":"So there are a lot of reforms we could do"},{"time":647546,"text":"that will counteract this."}]},{"cues":[{"time":648718,"text":"For example, this \"Citizens United\" ruling is a disaster,"},{"time":651938,"text":"because it means there's like a money gun aimed at your head,"},{"time":654137,"text":"and if you step out of line, if you try to reach across the aisle,"},{"time":656902,"text":"there's a ton of money waiting to be given to your opponent"},{"time":659418,"text":"to make everybody think that you are a terrible person through negative advertising."}]},{"cues":[{"time":665083,"text":"But the third class of reforms is that we've got to change"},{"time":667386,"text":"the nature of social relationships in Congress."},{"time":670213,"text":"The politicians I've met are generally very extroverted,"},{"time":674524,"text":"friendly, very socially skillful people,"},{"time":677595,"text":"and that's the nature of politics. You've got to make relationships,"},{"time":680949,"text":"make deals, you've got to cajole, please, flatter,"},{"time":684228,"text":"you've got to use your personal skills,"},{"time":686613,"text":"and that's the way politics has always worked."},{"time":689004,"text":"But beginning in the 1990s, first the House of Representatives"},{"time":692084,"text":"changed its legislative calendar"},{"time":694469,"text":"so that all business is basically done in the middle of the week."},{"time":698125,"text":"Nowadays, Congressmen fly in on Tuesday morning,"},{"time":700354,"text":"they do battle for two days, then they fly home Thursday afternoon."},{"time":703203,"text":"They don't move their families to the District."},{"time":705108,"text":"They don't meet each other's spouses or children."},{"time":707426,"text":"There's no more relationship there."},{"time":709940,"text":"And trying to run Congress without human relationships"},{"time":713736,"text":"is like trying to run a car without motor oil."},{"time":716563,"text":"Should we be surprised when the whole thing freezes up"},{"time":719400,"text":"and descends into paralysis and polarization?"},{"time":723233,"text":"A simple change to the legislative calendar,"},{"time":724984,"text":"such as having business stretch out for three weeks"},{"time":727311,"text":"and then they get a week off to go home,"},{"time":728874,"text":"that would change the fundamental relationships in Congress."}]},{"cues":[{"time":732199,"text":"So there's a lot we can do, but who's going to push them to do it?"},{"time":735335,"text":"There are a number of groups that are working on this."},{"time":737719,"text":"No Labels and Common Cause, I think,"},{"time":739871,"text":"have very good ideas for changes we need to do"},{"time":742010,"text":"to make our democracy more responsive and our Congress more effective."}]},{"cues":[{"time":745175,"text":"But I'd like to supplement their work"},{"time":746998,"text":"with a little psychological trick, and the trick is this."},{"time":751062,"text":"Nothing pulls people together like a common threat"},{"time":754112,"text":"or a common attack, especially an attack from a foreign enemy,"},{"time":757905,"text":"unless of course that threat hits on our polarized psychology,"},{"time":763227,"text":"in which case, as I said before, it can actually pull us apart."},{"time":766181,"text":"Sometimes a single threat can polarize us, as we saw."},{"time":769104,"text":"But what if the situation we face is not a single threat"},{"time":772214,"text":"but is actually more like this,"},{"time":774051,"text":"where there's just so much stuff coming in,"},{"time":775481,"text":"it's just, \"Start shooting, come on, everybody,"},{"time":777562,"text":"we've got to just work together, just start shooting.\""},{"time":779812,"text":"Because actually, we do face this situation."},{"time":782437,"text":"This is where we are as a country."}]},{"cues":[{"time":784973,"text":"So here's another asteroid."},{"time":787167,"text":"We've all seen versions of this graph, right,"},{"time":788843,"text":"which shows the changes in wealth since 1979,"},{"time":792677,"text":"and as you can see, almost all the gains in wealth"},{"time":795276,"text":"have gone to the top 20 percent, and especially the top one percent."},{"time":800170,"text":"Rising inequality like this is associated"},{"time":802298,"text":"with so many problems for a democracy."},{"time":804971,"text":"Especially, it destroys our ability to trust each other,"},{"time":807939,"text":"to feel that we're all in the same boat, because it's obvious we're not."},{"time":811392,"text":"Some of us are sitting there safe and sound in gigantic private yachts."},{"time":814350,"text":"Other people are clinging to a piece of driftwood."},{"time":815940,"text":"We're not all in the same boat, and that means"},{"time":817992,"text":"nobody's willing to sacrifice for the common good."},{"time":822901,"text":"The left has been screaming about this asteroid for 30 years now,"},{"time":825777,"text":"and the right says, \"Huh, what? Hmm? No problem. No problem.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":830719,"text":"Now,"},{"time":833298,"text":"why is that happening to us? Why is the inequality rising?"},{"time":835647,"text":"Well, one of the largest causes, after globalization,"},{"time":839265,"text":"is actually this fourth asteroid,"},{"time":842111,"text":"rising non-marital births."},{"time":844086,"text":"This graph shows the steady rise of out-of-wedlock births"},{"time":847022,"text":"since the 1960s."},{"time":849000,"text":"Most Hispanic and black children are now born to unmarried mothers."},{"time":852279,"text":"Whites are headed that way too."},{"time":854687,"text":"Within a decade or two, most American children"},{"time":857032,"text":"will be born into homes with no father."},{"time":859901,"text":"This means that there's much less money coming into the house."},{"time":862255,"text":"But it's not just money. It's also stability versus chaos."},{"time":866213,"text":"As I know from working with street children in Brazil,"},{"time":868448,"text":"Mom's boyfriend is often a really, really dangerous person for kids."}]},{"cues":[{"time":873510,"text":"Now the right has been screaming about this asteroid since the 1960s,"},{"time":877527,"text":"and the left has been saying, \"It's not a problem. It's not a problem.\""},{"time":881406,"text":"The left has been very reluctant to say"},{"time":883112,"text":"that marriage is actually good for women and for children."},{"time":886717,"text":"Now let me be clear. I'm not blaming the women here."},{"time":888678,"text":"I'm actually more critical of the men"},{"time":890172,"text":"who won't take responsibility for their own children"},{"time":892165,"text":"and of an economic system that makes it difficult"},{"time":894996,"text":"for many men to earn enough money to support those children."},{"time":898229,"text":"But even if you blame nobody, it still is a national problem,"},{"time":902597,"text":"and one side has been more concerned about it than the other."},{"time":906332,"text":"The New York Times finally noticed this asteroid"},{"time":908565,"text":"with a front-page story last July"},{"time":910845,"text":"showing how the decline of marriage contributes to inequality."}]},{"cues":[{"time":915059,"text":"We are becoming a nation of just two classes."},{"time":918653,"text":"When Americans go to college and marry each other,"},{"time":921395,"text":"they have very low divorce rates."},{"time":924095,"text":"They earn a lot of money, they invest that money in their kids,"},{"time":927140,"text":"some of them become tiger mothers,"},{"time":928683,"text":"the kids rise to their full potential,"},{"time":930359,"text":"and the kids go on to become"},{"time":932782,"text":"the top two lines in this graph."},{"time":937073,"text":"And then there's everybody else:"},{"time":939703,"text":"the children who don't benefit from a stable marriage,"},{"time":942947,"text":"who don't have as much invested in them,"},{"time":944650,"text":"who don't grow up in a stable environment,"},{"time":946434,"text":"and who go on to become the bottom three lines in that graph."}]},{"cues":[{"time":951392,"text":"So once again, we see that these two graphs are actually saying the same thing."},{"time":954957,"text":"As before, we've got a problem, we've got to start working on this,"},{"time":957971,"text":"we've got to do something,"},{"time":960003,"text":"and what's wrong with you people that you don't see my threat?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":962643,"text":"But if everybody could just take off their partisan blinders,"},{"time":966445,"text":"we'd see that these two problems actually"},{"time":969048,"text":"are best addressed together."},{"time":971795,"text":"Because if you really care about income inequality,"},{"time":973538,"text":"you might want to talk to some evangelical Christian groups"},{"time":975845,"text":"that are working on ways to promote marriage."},{"time":978976,"text":"But then you're going to run smack into the problem"},{"time":981182,"text":"that women don't generally want to marry someone"},{"time":983710,"text":"who doesn't have a job."},{"time":986062,"text":"So if you really care about strengthening families,"},{"time":987875,"text":"you might want to talk to some liberal groups"},{"time":989536,"text":"who are working on promoting educational equality,"},{"time":992942,"text":"who are working on raising the minimum wage,"},{"time":994702,"text":"who are working on finding ways to stop so many men"},{"time":997542,"text":"from being sucked into the criminal justice system and"},{"time":999581,"text":"taken out of the marriage market for their whole lives."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1002935,"text":"So to conclude, there are at least four asteroids headed our way."},{"time":1008783,"text":"How many of you can see all four?"},{"time":1011575,"text":"Please raise your hand right now if you're willing to admit"},{"time":1014190,"text":"that all four of these are national problems."},{"time":1017183,"text":"Please raise your hands."},{"time":1019040,"text":"Okay, almost all of you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1020687,"text":"Well, congratulations, you guys are the inaugural members"},{"time":1023529,"text":"of the Asteroids Club, which is a club"},{"time":1026792,"text":"for all Americans who are willing to admit"},{"time":1030033,"text":"that the other side actually might have a point."},{"time":1032936,"text":"In the Asteroids Club, we don't start by looking for common ground."},{"time":1035967,"text":"Common ground is often very hard to find."},{"time":1037861,"text":"No, we start by looking for common threats"},{"time":1040045,"text":"because common threats make common ground."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1043714,"text":"Now, am I being naive? Is it naive to think"},{"time":1047538,"text":"that people could ever lay down their swords,"},{"time":1048909,"text":"and left and right could actually work together?"},{"time":1052515,"text":"I don't think so, because it happens,"},{"time":1055002,"text":"not all that often, but there are a variety of examples that point the way."},{"time":1058866,"text":"This is something we can do."},{"time":1060305,"text":"Because Americans on both sides care about the decline in civility,"},{"time":1064340,"text":"and they've formed dozens of organizations,"},{"time":1066091,"text":"at the national level, such as this one,"},{"time":1068264,"text":"down to many local organizations,"},{"time":1069912,"text":"such as To The Village Square in Tallahassee, Florida,"},{"time":1072270,"text":"which tries to bring state leaders together to help facilitate"},{"time":1074745,"text":"that sort of working together human relationship"},{"time":1078191,"text":"that's necessary to solve Florida's problems."},{"time":1081231,"text":"Americans on both sides care about global poverty and AIDS,"},{"time":1085626,"text":"and on so many humanitarian issues,"},{"time":1088522,"text":"liberals and evangelicals are actually natural allies,"},{"time":1091546,"text":"and at times they really have worked together"},{"time":1093429,"text":"to solve these problems."},{"time":1095346,"text":"And most surprisingly to me, they sometimes can even see"},{"time":1098069,"text":"eye to eye on criminal justice."},{"time":1100065,"text":"For example, the incarceration rate, the prison population"},{"time":1104018,"text":"in this country has quadrupled since 1980."},{"time":1107971,"text":"Now this is a social disaster,"},{"time":1110555,"text":"and liberals are very concerned about this."},{"time":1112607,"text":"The Southern Poverty Law Center is often fighting"},{"time":1115394,"text":"the prison-industrial complex, fighting to prevent a system"},{"time":1118266,"text":"that's just sucking in more and more poor young men."},{"time":1121044,"text":"But are conservatives happy about this?"},{"time":1123377,"text":"Well, Grover Norquist isn't, because this system"},{"time":1126459,"text":"costs an unbelievable amount of money."},{"time":1129531,"text":"And so, because the prison-industrial complex"},{"time":1132110,"text":"is bankrupting our states and corroding our souls,"},{"time":1136347,"text":"groups of fiscal conservatives and Christian conservatives"},{"time":1140079,"text":"have come together to form a group called Right on Crime."},{"time":1143911,"text":"And at times they have worked with the Southern Poverty Law Center"},{"time":1146567,"text":"to oppose the building of new prisons"},{"time":1148545,"text":"and to work for reforms that will make the justice system"},{"time":1151886,"text":"more efficient and more humane."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1155007,"text":"So this is possible. We can do it."},{"time":1158302,"text":"Let us therefore go to battle stations,"},{"time":1161383,"text":"not to fight each other,"},{"time":1162642,"text":"but to begin deflecting these incoming asteroids."},{"time":1165968,"text":"And let our first mission be to press Congress"},{"time":1169039,"text":"to reform itself, before it's too late for our nation."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1172982,"text":"Thank you. (Applause)"}]}]}